Adding these gives:

Since no subsequent transaction affects the paid-in capital account (the other transactions are purchases, expenses, sales, etc.), the paid‐in capital remains unchanged throughout the period.

Thus the paid‐in capital on the balance sheet is:
• Paid-in Capital Initial Value: 13,000,000.00 
• Paid-in Capital End Value: 13,000,000.00
